import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    median_delay = data['delay'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_delay, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Delay: {median_delay:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=['Average Distance'], y=[average_distance], palette='viridis')
    ax.axhline(average_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {average_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_count = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data_pivot = data_count.pivot('origin', 'destination', 'count')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(data_pivot, cmap='viridis', annot=True, fmt='.0f')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination pairs have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of delay over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Delay'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of delay time by origin?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay Time')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
